  112-## Release notes - version 3.1.21, 3.2.9
  --
  148-   * `TypeConverter` can be set only when creating a new context, the setter won't work anymore
  149-   * Implementation of the `MemberAccess` is required when crearting a new context, you must always provide your own
  150-   * `DefaultMemberAccess` is only available in tests, it won't be used when there was no custom `MemberAccess` provided, an exception will be thrown in such case
  151: * sets source and target in `pom.xml` to Java 1.7
  152- * makes better decisions on methods first call [#39](../../../pull/39) -
  153-   thanks to Yasser Zamani
  154: * fixes access to property which reads method is Java 8 default method [#33](../../../pull/33) -
  155-   thanks to Yanming Zhou
  156-
  157-## Release notes - version 3.1.15, 3.0.21
  --
  191-   thanks to Christian Niessner from [secadm GmbH](http://www.secadm.de/)
  192-
  193-## Release notes - version 3.1.4
  194: * fixes issue with executing expressions on Java 8 plus adds an `java like` method matching [#19](../../../pull/19) -
  195-   thanks to marvkis
  196-
  197-## Release notes - version 3.1.3, 3.0.14, 3.0.6.1
  --
  213-## Release notes - version 3.0.12
  214- * lots of optimizations which should improve overall performance [#9](../../../pull/9), [#10](../../../pull/10), [#11](../../../pull/11), [#12](../../../pull/12) - 
  215-   thanks to Daniel Fernández
  216: * OGNL supports default methods in interfaces (Java 8) [OGNL-249](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OGNL-249)
  217-
  218-## Release notes - version 3.0.11
  219- * fixes problem with cacheKey too expensive to create [WW-4485 ](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WW-4485 ) -
  --
  252- * small fix to improve performance [WW-3580](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WW-3580)
  253-
  254-## Release notes - version 3.0.2
  255: * small fix to solve a problem with compiling under JDK5
  256-
  257-## Release notes - version 3.0.1
  258: * Javassist added back as a dependency [WW-3544](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WW-3544)
