[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test setup needs**\n\nI think we need to determine if the current failure is due to an improper setup for the Forge workflow. It seems that the test logic assertion changed in version 3.3.5, and the agent may need to fix the tests. I’m wondering about the deterministic setup—if there are extra dependencies, like javascript or Docker involved? Checking the existing build's JVM arguments for `add-opens` might be necessary, especially for dealing with any JDK internals. Existing tests passed except for one assertion. So maybe we don’t need to change the setup right now.\n\n**Investigating Java run issue**\n\nI’m looking into a failing Java run, and I’m wondering if it’s related to an environment property. Maybe I could set `ognl.security.manager=forceDisableOnInit`? It appears that the existing tests set this property for each test. With OGNL 3.3.5 and JDK 25, does the SecurityManager get removed? I think it’s important to check the version notes to clarify that. This could be key in figuring out why things aren’t working.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04236a9044683c91016a3ef4e2f51081909b3c06c282de8c55\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPvTpwaXFOebX5Cd55KgXwdr03FrvgLpgJS-TWom5U7jfQ0UiQ5TGqne1LTdcjBHQlVxVT6Ng8SyKNjgUT-r0Vivy6eGq5VRUsqF3BN9RkYwxouKH88phCJdDsGtonfo8kZIBKZzPuoJNk8cU4pAjhCEcHUF13ee8brYrt3gsIeXADp9_K7vCWVhzmXaRUClznE04POebPrhPY3Jsgf05Mnm85Gdu63I_JeBoXFBCiFA1k22tvmR38zsD-B-qNctdcFK7OrmftCABpsooCPPaZwK9C70kgnaaTaB3nLypffdM-vUkOFkW87rjdo6vyFTISbh8GxNcJJ4iGA_XYyNZLY7jP4-8Dv91i9xUayhnhLX-sjRFMl0C3nNgNU34aX1IPKZyfDYPR7oHjBvav0WDQU_rGw67-rSMFPD3S3IdTY8g9zXVhuzBPOkqVcAIAxvAyy2ZCi9kkQhfVSbQXhAM8N53VFU-AmHxOMEh0a-vqXwvui61BOGjJTbbNd77tFTjjvURBw-4iOSEgjJhyy42O9fO9qyJCtOa0ZmPPAzfhnRf0N5m0jqYy08I_nC0s9acb5YIs0biQ0g2OdqDUhWFHiwpnIy-PLHmOttAQEEDRZ1R_YTrneEgCp2lduwHrHiTN-8k_F51BBch0hPbsF_BM1n3sRpBfZ3tp9Da83xRGmSy